results.name: The non-octal numbers: numbers containing an 8 or 9 (they cannot be mistaken for octal numbers).
example: '42' might be read as an octal number, but '48' could not be and so belongs to the sequence.
results.author: Thomas Schulze (jazariel(AT)tiscalenet.it), Sep 12 2000
